explanation:
The report is correct. With OS_DEBUG defined as an empty macro (#define OS_DEBUG(__VA_ARGS__)), the statement

    OS_DEBUG("read: %s\n", strerror(errno));

preprocesses to just a semicolon (a null statement). That null statement is an operation that will be executed at runtime but has no effect; removing it would not change program behaviour. By the MISRA C 2023 definition cited ("Any operation that is executed but whose removal would not affect program behaviour constitutes dead code"), this is dead code and therefore violates Rule 2.2. (Note: the original logging call and its side‑effects are not present because the macro expansion removes the call and its argument evaluation.)
